# Afrolink News API

A production‑ready RESTful API for a news platform where authors publish content, readers consume it, and an analytics engine tracks engagement. Built with **Node.js + TypeScript** following best practices: role‑based access control, soft deletion, read tracking with spam protection, and daily analytics aggregation via job queue.

## 🚀 Live Demo (if deployed)
> *No live deployment – run locally using the instructions below.*

## 📚 Technology Stack

- **Runtime**: Node.js (v18+)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Framework**: Express.js
- **ORM**: Prisma (with PostgreSQL)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (Docker or local)
- **Cache/Queue**: Redis + Bull (for rate limiting and analytics job queue)
- **Authentication**: JWT (bcrypt for password hashing)
- **Validation**: Zod
- **Scheduler**: node-cron (daily analytics at 00:00 GMT)
- **Testing**: Jest + Supertest (planned)
- **Dev Tools**: Nodemon, ts-node

## ✨ Features (User Stories Implemented)

| User Story | Endpoints | Status |
|------------|-----------|--------|
| 1. Secure Signup & Authentication | `POST /api/auth/signup` | ✅ |
| 2. Login & JWT | `POST /api/auth/login` | ✅ |
| 3. Article Lifecycle (Author only) | `POST /api/articles`, `GET /api/articles/me`, `PUT /api/articles/:id`, `DELETE /api/articles/:id` | ✅ |
| 4. Public News Feed (filtering, pagination, exclude deleted) | `GET /api/articles` (published feed) | ✅ |
| 5. Read Tracking (with spam protection) | `GET /api/feed/:id` | ✅ |
| 6. Analytics Engine (daily aggregation via Bull queue + cron) | Background job | ✅ |
| 7. Author Performance Dashboard | `GET /author/dashboard` | ✅ |
| 8. Author Content List (including drafts) | `GET /api/articles/me` | ✅ |

**Bonus implemented**:
- Rate limiter (Redis) to prevent refreshing the same article >5 times per 10 seconds.
- Unit tests structure (mocked database) – ready to expand.

## 🛠️ Setup & Installation

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18+)
- PostgreSQL (Docker recommended) or local installation
- Redis (Docker recommended)

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/AbebeTefera/afrolink-news-api.git
cd afrolink-news-api